records.addlTxt:
Defendant Joshua J Dodd in court, in custody, with attorney Katie B. Bricco.   Michael Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court strikes the repeater and finds defendant guilty.     The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS 6 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT; (consecutive to any other sentence);
  -  1 YEAR 6 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  Any Walmart in Waukesha County.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are pruchased, used, stored, packaged or distributed.

RESTITUTION:  $392.00 (payable to Walmart listed in criminal complaint - to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
